posts.description:
Join us for a curated photography exhibit, featuring TechWomen and the communities across the globe that we are impacting.

Since 2011, TechWomen has been empowering women to be change agents ¨C exposing more women and children to STEM and leading efforts to address social and economic challenges. Last year, TechWomen awarded $15,000 in seed grants to support six action plans. Read about the top 2015 action plans. Donations from the expo will fund 2016 seed grants. 

Please RSVP: http://bit.ly/1OP7uMh

Bring your friends for an opporutnity to share what TechWomen is about. Refreshments and light bites will be served.

FAQs

What is the admission fee?

The event is free. We are collecting donations, of which 100% will go toward 2016 TechWomen seed grants.

What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?

White Walls SF is a 12-to 15-minute walk from both Civic Center and Powell St. BART stations. We strongly encourage attendees to take public transportation to the venue.

Can I extend this invitation to others?

Yes, we welcome you to invite others who will want to learn about and support TechWomen.

Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?

We will be checking RSVPs by name. Please bring a digital copy or printed copy of your ticket with you to the event.

posts.message:
The mission of TechWomen Exchange Program is to empower, connect, and support the next generation of women leaders in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) by providing them a unique experience in the United States to advance their careers, pursue their dreams, and become role models for women and girls in Morocco. Women committed to addressing concerns of global climate change and environmental issues are particularly encouraged to apply.

The program is made for women in STEM who meet the following criteria: 

?	Have a minimum of two years full-time professional experience in the STEM fields (science, technology, engineering and math)
?	Have, at minimum, a bachelor¡¯s degree/four year university degree or equivalent
?	Be proficient in written and spoken English

For complete eligibility information, program details and selection timeline, please view the TechWomen website at https://goo.gl/A14nSV. 

**** Deadline to submit applications is February 1, 2016 ****

posts.message: WITI - Women In Technology International Summit, June 5-7 in San Jose, is the annual gathering of tech-savvy women, held in the heart of Silicon Valley.  Executive women, entrepreneurs, and technology thought leaders from around the world converge to collaborate on innovative solutions to common business challenges; explore new business opportunities that underscore how technology is powering change; and build and expand strong connections in a welcoming networking environment of women committed to helping each other succeed.    Use code WOMEN for $200 discount off the prevailing cost of a 3-day pass.  www.witi.com/summit

posts.message: Girls in Tech is proud to announce the fourth annual #CatalystConference, a three-day event designed to celebrate women in this new age of innovation! posts.message:
On Feb. 26-28th we will be hosting our annual LAUNCH HACKATHON featuring 1,500 developers and designers competing over 48 hours to build an exceptional MVP, proof of concept, and demo. 

The top 10 Hacakthon projects will present on the LAUNCH Festival Main Stage, and the top four will be invited to join my incubator¡ªthe LAUNCH Incubator¡ªwhich is a12 week program and comes with a $250,000 investment. If you want to bring a team, or come as an individual developer, register here! 

Also, if you've got a friends or potential teammates who think should be at this event, please forward them this email and ask them to register. http://www.launchhackathon.com/register
